A sombre Caroline Kennedy attended a memorial today for those killed in the nuclear strike on August 6, 1945, in Hiroshima.

The US ambassador to Japan attended the ceremony to those killed 69-years ago wearing a plastic raincoat the guest of honor sat near to Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe.

Kennedy, 56, who first visited Hiroshima in 1978 with her uncle Senator Edward Kenney is the second US ambassador to ever attend the even that honors the 140,000 people who died in the US nuclear attack on the city.

